The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 11: Switzerland is ready to help India on the issue of black money stashed in its banks. Under international pressure, Switzerland has changed its attitude concerning tax havens and is ready to give assistance in this regard to India, former member of Parliament Rudolf Strahm said.                             
	 New Delhi, March 11: Hero Honda is conducting a feasibility study to find a suitable location to set up its fourth manufacturing facility. Managing director Pawan Munjal said a decision would be taken over the next six months.                             
	 New Delhi, March 11: NMDCs follow-on public offer gained momentum on the second day of the issue, with institutional investors coming in. The issue received bids for over 26.09 crore shares, or 79 per cent of the 33.22 crore shares put on the block.                            
	 New Delhi, March 11: US-based Dominos Pizza today said Indias share in its global revenue would increase substantially in the near future. The country would become one of its top five revenue garners within three years.                            
	 Mumbai, March 11: The State Bank of India has received the permission from the Chinese government to lend in the local currency  Yuan, a top official today said. The SBI is the first Indian bank to receive this permission from the China.
                                                                                                                          
